Discover Clinical Trials Easily with Criteria-Based Search and Filter.

Reduce the time it takes candidates to discover clinical trials by adding the Criteria-Based Search and Filter to your Experience Cloud site. With Criteria-Based Search and Filter, you can customize a unified searchable field that helps users easily search for and find clinical trials based on conditions, keywords, or the name of the disease. You can provide sorting options for search results displayed as cards so that it's easy for participants to navigate through matching trials. You can also set up trial search targeting options based on their location to help participants find more suitable trials effectively.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions with Life Sciences Cloud and Participant Enrollment Add-On license.

When: Participant Management is available starting in June 2024.

Who: This feature is available to users with the Criteria-Based Search and Filter permission set license.

How: From Setup, find Criteria-Based Search and Filter, and turn on Criteria-Based Search and Filter. Next, go to the Data Pipelines setup page and turn on data pipelines. Then, clone and activate the Research Study Searchable Field DPE definition. In a new or existing Experience Cloud site, create a standard page for searching, add it as a menu item, and make the page publicly available.
